Introduction

VICTON is a six-member boy group currently under IST Entertainment, formerly called Play M Entertainment. They officially debuted on November 9, 2016, with the mini album 'Voice To New World'.

On July 19, 2019, Han Seung Woo ranked third in the survival reality Produce X 101, becoming a member of group X1 with an exclusive two-and-a-half-year contract. However, the group disbanded on January 6, 2020, and on the 29th, it was announced that he would return to activities with VICTON.

In April 2023, Dohanse, Byungchan, and Subin left IST Entertainment after the expiration of their exclusive contracts. Meanwhile, Han Seung Woo, Seungsik, and Sejun remained in the agency due to the contract period adjustment for their military service. Following this, the members will focus on individual activities for the time being.

On December 17th, 2024, it was announced that Kang Seungsik and Lim Sejun would be ending their contracts, leading to the departure of all members from the company. However, this does not indicate a disbandment, making their future uncertain.
